# How to set up Turso (FREE - 9GB storage, 500 databases):
#
# 1. Sign up at https://turso.tech (free account)
#
# 2. Install Turso CLI:
#    curl -sSfL https://get.tur.so/install.sh | bash
#
# 3. Login to Turso:
#    turso auth login
#
# 4. Create your database:
#    turso db create personal-finance
#
# 5. Get the database URL:
#    turso db show personal-finance --url
#    Copy the URL and paste it as TURSO_DATABASE_URL above
#
# 6. Create an auth token:
#    turso db tokens create personal-finance
#    Copy the token and paste it as TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN above
#
# 7. For local development, create a .env.local file with your credentials:
#    TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://your-database-url.turso.io
#    TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-token-here
#
# 8. For Vercel deployment:
#    - Go to your project settings on Vercel
#    - Add Environment Variables with the same names
#    - Redeploy your app
#
# That's it! Your multi-user finance tracker is ready to use!
